Based on my comprehensive web search, there is no standalone MCP server or tool specifically named **"parse_video"** as of 2025–2026. However, there are several closely related MCP servers that provide video parsing/analysis capabilities. Here's a summary of the most relevant findings:

---

## Closest Match: `douyin-mcp-server` (抖音 MCP Server)

The tool `parse_douyin_video_info` (sometimes invoked as `parse_douyin_video`) is part of the **douyin-mcp-server** by [yzfly](https://github.com/yzfly/douyin-mcp-server). It parses Douyin (TikTok China) video info from share links.

**Configuration (Claude Desktop):**
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "douyin-mcp": {
      "command": "uvx",
      "args": ["douyin-mcp-server"],
      "env": {
        "DASHSCOPE_API_KEY": "your-api-key-here"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Available tools:**
| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `parse_douyin_video_info` | Parse video metadata (title, author, etc.) without downloading |
| `get_douyin_download_link` | Get watermark-free download URL |
| `extract_douyin_text` | Download video, extract audio, transcribe to text |

---

## Other Video MCP Servers (2025–2026)

### 1. **video-context-mcp-server** (npm: `video-context-mcp-server`)
Full-featured video analysis with frame extraction, transcription, Q&A.
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "video-context": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "video-context-mcp-server@latest"],
      "env": {
        "GLM_API_KEY": "your-key"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
**Tools:** `analyze_video`, `summarize_video`, `extract_frames`, `transcribe_video`, `search_timestamp`, `get_video_info`

### 2. **mcp-video-analyzer** (npm: `mcp-video-analyzer`)
Extracts transcripts, key frames with OCR, and annotated timelines. Supports Loom, MP4, WebM.
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "video-analyzer": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["mcp-video-analyzer@latest"]
    }
  }
}
```

### 3. **Video Vision MCP** (`@oamaestro/video-vision-mcp`)
Supports YouTube, TikTok, Instagram + 1000+ platforms via yt-dlp. Scene detection + Whisper transcription.
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "video-vision": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@oamaestro/video-vision-mcp"]
    }
  }
}
```

### 4. **media-transcriber-mcp** (Rust/Cargo)
Transcribes local audio/video using Whisper. Takes screenshots at timestamps.
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "media-transcriber": {
      "command": "media-transcriber-mcp",
      "args": []
    }
  }
}
```

### 5. **Video MCP Server** (`ethanbobbytr-videomcp`)
Keyframe extraction + Whisper transcription with caching.
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "video-mcp": {
      "command": "/path/to/venv/bin/video-mcp",
      "env": {
        "VIDEO_MCP_FRAME_INTERVAL_SECONDS": "10",
        "VIDEO_MCP_WHISPER_MODEL": "base",
        "VIDEO_MCP_USE_SCENE_DETECTION": "true"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

## Summary

If you were looking for **`parse_video`** specifically, it's most likely a reference to the **`parse_douyin_video_info`** tool from the `douyin-mcp-server` package (GitHub: [yzfly/douyin-mcp-server](https://github.com/yzfly/douyin-mcp-server), ~99 stars, MIT license, last updated July 2025). For general-purpose video parsing in MCP, **video-context-mcp-server** or **mcp-video-analyzer** are the most popular choices as of 2025–2026.

